31 37-1-12, Code of Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
32 "§37-1-1
33 A commission to be known as the Public Service
34 Commission, consisting of a president and two associates who
35 shall be competent persons and qualified electors of this
36 state, is established with seven commissioners as provided
37 under Section 37-1-3."
38 "§37-1-3
39 (a)(1) The terms of office of the commissioners shall
40 be for four years; at the election to be held in the state on
41 the first Tuesday after the first Monday in November, for all
42 commissioners serving on or before the effective date of this
43 act.
44 (2) At the general election held in November 1940, and
45 every four years thereafter until the general election held in
46 November 2028, a president of the commission shall be elected
47 by the qualified electors of this state; and at the general
48 election to be held in the state on the first Tuesday after
49 the first Monday held in November, 1942, and every four years
50 thereafter until the general election held in November 2026,
51 two associates, who, with the president, shall constitute the
52 commission, shall be elected by the qualified electors of the
53 state. The result of such election shall be ascertained and
54 declared by the same authority and in the same manner as are
55 the results of election for Chief Justice and associate
56 justices of the Supreme Court.
