61 after their election.
62 (b)(1) Beginning after the effective date of this act,
63 the membership of the commission shall be expanded so that
64 each commissioner shall represent and serve a geographical
65 district that shall be identical to a corresponding
66 congressional district, as fixed and established by Section
67 17-14-70 or pursuant to any map ordered by a court to be used
68 in lieu thereof. Each commissioner must have been a resident
69 of the state for a period of seven years immediately before
70 taking office and reside in the state while in office. The
71 Secretary of State and Governor shall ensure that
72 commissioners are phased in so that each of the seven
73 congressional districts are represented by the terms beginning
74 in January 2031.
75 (2) No later than July 15, 2026, the Governor shall
76 appoint four commissioners to serve initial terms, two of whom
77 shall serve a two-year term and two of whom shall serve a
78 four-year term. When making appointments, the Governor shall
79 choose one individual from a list of three names submitted for
80 each position. The lists shall be jointly submitted by the
81 Lieutenant Governor, the Speaker of the House of
82 Representatives, and the President Pro Tempore of the Senate.
83 The lists shall be provided to the Governor no later than June
84 1, 2026.
