144 "§37-1-12
145 (a)(1) Beginning January 19, 2027, the position of
146 Secretary of Energy is created as a member of the Governor's
147 cabinet. The secretary shall be appointed by and serve at the
148 pleasure of the Governor. The secretary's salary shall be
149 fixed by the Governor and shall not be subject to Section
150 36-6-6. The secretary must have experience in utility
151 regulation or energy policy or a related field.
152 (2) The Secretary of Energy shall direct the activities
153 of the commission and shall set the agendas for all meetings
154 of the commissioners, provided a meeting agenda may be amended
155 by the affirmative vote of at least five commissioners.
156 (3) The Secretary of Energy shall have authority over
157 personnel and administrative functions of the commission.
158 (4) The Secretary of Energy shall be subject to the
159 ethics laws under Chapter 25 of Title 36.
160 (b) The commissionsecretary, under the provisions of
161 the merit systemMerit System, shall have the authority to
162 appoint or employ professional and administrative employees,
163 including attorneys, officers, and such accountants,
164 engineers, experts, inspectors, and other clerks and other
165 employees as are necessary or expedient to carry out the
166 duties conferred by law upon the commission., and the salaries
167 thereforThe salaries of all employees shall be fixed according
168 to the provisions of the merit systemMerit System. The
